    "# üìñ Chapter 1: Understanding Risk Management\n",
    "\n",
    "## üé≠ The Delegate's Perspective\n",
    "\n",
    "Fund managers, endowment managers, and professional delegated money managers rarely can allocate capital freely. The ultimate investors impose various restrictions:\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Static Constraints**\n",
    "- üö´ **Sector restrictions**: Limitations on investment sectors\n",
    "- üìâ **Short-selling restrictions**: Constraints on going short\n",
    "- üí∞ **Leverage restrictions**: Limits on explicit leverage use\n",
    "- üìä **Derivative restrictions**: Controls on derivative and embedded leverage\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Dynamic Constraints**\n",
    "- üìà **Risk limits**: Portfolio variance must stay below specified thresholds\n",
    "- üéØ **Tracking error constraints**: Limits on deviation from benchmark performance\n",
    "\n",
    "> **üí° Key Insight**: What makes these dynamic constraints challenging is that risk is highly time-varying!\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
