    "# üìñ Chapter 2: From Maximum Losses to Portfolio Risk\n",
    "\n",
    "## üéØ Converting Loss Tolerance to Volatility Targets\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's build a framework for determining optimal portfolio risk based on your maximum acceptable loss.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **The Mathematical Framework**\n",
    "\n",
    "Given:\n",
    "- **L**: Maximum loss you're comfortable with (e.g., 20%)\n",
    "- **p**: Probability threshold (e.g., 5%)\n",
    "- **x**: Portfolio weight in risky assets\n",
    "- **$r_p$**: Portfolio return\n",
    "\n",
    "We want:\n",
    "$$\\text{Prob}(rf + xr_p \\leq -L) = p$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### **Derivation Steps**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Assume** $rf \\approx \\mu \\approx 0$ (reasonable for short horizons)\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Standardize** to normal distribution:\n",
    "   $$\\text{Prob}\\left(\\frac{xr_p}{x\\sigma(r_p)} \\leq -\\frac{L}{x\\sigma(r_p)}\\right) = p$$\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Apply** normal CDF:\n",
    "   $$F\\left(-\\frac{L}{x\\sigma(r_p)}\\right) = p$$\n",
    "\n",
    "4. **Solve** for portfolio volatility:\n",
    "   $$x\\sigma \\leq -\\frac{L}{F^{-1}(p)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
