    "# üìñ Chapter 3: Managing Factor Risk\n",
    "\n",
    "## üîç Variance Decomposition\n",
    "\n",
    "Understanding which factors drive portfolio risk is crucial for effective risk management.\n",
    "\n",
    "### **The Mathematics of Risk Attribution**\n",
    "\n",
    "For an asset with return:\n",
    "$$r^i_t = \\sum_j^m \\beta_{i,j}f^j_t + \\epsilon^i_t$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The variance share of factor j is:\n",
    "$$\\text{Factor Share}_j = \\frac{\\beta_{i,j}\\text{Cov}(r^i_t, f^j_t)}{\\text{Var}(r^i_t)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The idiosyncratic risk share is:\n",
    "$$\\text{Idiosyncratic Share} = \\frac{\\sigma^2_{\\epsilon}}{\\text{Var}(r^i_t)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's implement this decomposition:\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "variance-decomp",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# üìä Variance Decomposition Analysis\n",
    "# =====================================\n",
    "\n",
    "import statsmodels.api as sm\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example: Momentum ETF Analysis\n",
    "tickers = ['MTUM', 'SPMO', 'XMMO', 'IMTM', 'XSMO', 'PDP', 'JMOM', 'DWAS', 'VFMO', 'XSVM', 'QMOM']\n",
    "\n",
    "def perform_variance_decomposition(tickers, df_ETF, df_factor):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Perform variance decomposition for ETFs against factor model.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    VarianceDecomposition = pd.DataFrame([], index=tickers)\n",
    "    FactorLoadings = pd.DataFrame([], index=tickers)\n",
    "    VarianceIdiosyncratic = pd.DataFrame([], index=tickers, columns=['epsilon'])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for ticker in tickers:\n",
    "        y = df_ETF[ticker]\n",
    "        Factors = df_factor.drop(columns=['RF'])\n",
    "        X = sm.add_constant(Factors) \n",
    "        X = X[y.isna() == False]\n",
    "        y = y[y.isna() == False]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Run regression\n",
    "        model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Get covariance matrix\n",
    "        CovMatrix = pd.concat([y, X.iloc[:, 1:]], axis=1).cov()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Store results\n",
    "        FactorLoadings.loc[ticker, :] = model.params[1:]\n",
    "        VarianceIdiosyncratic.loc[ticker, 'epsilon'] = model.resid.var()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Calculate variance shares\n",
    "        for factor in Factors.columns:\n",
    "            VarianceDecomposition.loc[ticker, factor] = (\n",
    "                model.params[factor] * CovMatrix.loc[factor, ticker] / y.var() * 100\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Add residual variance share\n",
    "        VarianceDecomposition.loc[ticker, 'epsilon'] = model.resid.var() / y.var() * 100\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return VarianceDecomposition, FactorLoadings, VarianceIdiosyncratic\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize results\n",
    "def visualize_variance_decomposition(VarianceDecomposition):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Create visualization of variance decomposition.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Create stacked bar chart\n",
    "    VarianceDecomposition.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=ax, \n",
    "                               colormap='tab20', width=0.8)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax.set_title('üìä Variance Decomposition Across ETFs', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold', pad=20)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('ETF Ticker', fontsize=12)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Variance Share (%)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "    ax.legend(title='Risk Factors', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')\n",
    "    ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim([0, 100])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add percentage labels\n",
    "    for container in ax.containers:\n",
    "        ax.bar_label(container, fmt='%.0f', label_type='center', fontsize=8)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"‚úÖ Variance decomposition functions ready!\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nüìà Key Applications:\")\n",
    "print(\"   ‚Ä¢ Style analysis for manager classification\")\n",
    "print(\"   ‚Ä¢ Portfolio factor risk control\")\n",
    "print(\"   ‚Ä¢ Investment mandate compliance\")"
